inn1.comm: good length delivery defended to mid-off.
outside the off stump and left alone.
back of a length way outside the off stump, pitches and moves away.
gets behind it and defends behind point.
stays in the crease and plays towards gully.
plays forward and guides it towards gullly.
pushes to mid-on.
outside the off stump and left alone.
outside off stump and swinging away, left alone.
a bouncer over the head of the batsman.
swings away outside the off stump, left alone.
full and straight and hits Masakadza on the pads right in front, a loud shout, that was close, not given. Was looking to work it through the onside.
looking to work it through the onside, gets a leading edge over the slips to the third man fence, was in an awkward position when he played it.
played to the onside.
good ball from back of a length, hits him in the mid-riff.
outside the off stump and left alone.
way outside the off stump and left alone.
another leave outside the off stump.
full length delivery and looking to drive through the off side, gets an inside edge to square leg.
comes forward and defends square of the wicket on the off side.
driven in the air through point to the deep.
defends to point.
outside the off stump, left alone.
short down the leg side.
short and wide outside the off stump, cut in the air to the cover fence.
length delivery and strikes the pad in line, another decision not given.
lets it go through to the keeper.
plays forward towards backward point.
good length delivery angled in, left alone.
back of a length delivery outside the off stump, left alone.
full delivery driven through backward point to the fence for a boundary.
full on the legs and clipped to the midwicket fence.
outside the off stump and left alone.
extra bounce from a good length, left alone.
driven wide of mid-off for a single.
good length delivery coming in, left alone.
outside the off stump and left alone.
plays behind point.
full delivery driven through covers to the deep.
left alone outside the off stump.
short of a length delivery pulled to the onside.
driven back down the track.
outside the off stump and left alone.
yorker length delivery dug out to the off side.
turned away to long leg for a single.
beats the outside edge of the bat and through to the keeper.
outside the off stump and left alone.
full delivery driven through mid-on to the fence.
left alone through to the keeper.
full delivery pushed to mid-on.
pushed through the off side for a single.
cuts in and off the pad to the off side.
extra bounce and hits the glove, drops to the onside.
short ball and pulled away behind square leg to the fence.
cut away towards third slip.
driven firmly back to the bowler and he does well, sicks his left hand.
looking to whip it away, off the pad to the off side.
plays forward and gets an inside edge to the off side.
outside the off stump and left alone.
comes forward and defends to the off side.
comes forward way outside the off stump and plays, strikes the pad.
slashes and gets beaten.
driven to extra cover.
cut away behind point.
backs away and pushes to mid-on.
pulled to deep midwicket.
once again pulled to the onside.
way outside the off stump and Sibanda drives in the air to mid-off, Oram takes the catch.
defended down the track.
off the pad behind square leg.
good length delivery defended to the off side.
cut away to deep backward point.
way outside the off stump and left alone.
defended to the off side.
cut away down to third man.
full delivery way outside the off stump, left alone.
full on the legs, clipped to square leg.
defended down the track.
thickish edge to square leg.
comes out of the crease and looks to go big, but then changes his mind and defends.
makes room this time and looks to go big through the off side, gets beaten.
good length delivery defended to the off side.
pushes it wide of mid-on for a single.
short ball and Maskadza pulls straight down to Williamson at deep backward square leg.
plays to the off side.
way outside the off stump, left alone.
lets it go outside the off stump.
once again lets it go outside the off stump.
defends to the onside.
another leave outside the off stump.
pushes wide of mid-on for a single.
off the pad to the onside.
comes forward and blocks to the onside.
left alone outside the off stump.
skews off the outside edge to gully.
off the pad to the onside.
way down the leg side, an appeal for nothing.
in the block-hole and dug out to midwicket.
plays it down to fine leg.
good length delivery pitches and comes back in and takes the off stump for a toss as Taibu played down the wrong line.
way outside the off stump and very full, reaches it and drives to the cover fence.
played through square leg.
back of a length and coming in,
outside the off stump and left alone.
off the pad to the onside.
back of a length and angled across, shoulders arms.
played past the two close in fielders on the onside to the deep.
full toss on the legs and flicked away to the backward square leg fence.
nudges it down to long leg for a single.
short of a length and coming in, the batsman shoulders arms.
digs it out to mid-on.
defends down the track.
way outside the off stump and left alone.
turned to the onside to midwicket.
length delivery defended to the off side.
slower delivery and keeps a touch low, defended.
works it forward of square one the onside and picks up a single.
good length delivery defended down the track.
pitches short of a length and coming in, played with the angled to square leg.
full and in the slot, driven nicely past the mid-off fielder to the fence.
defends down the track.
plays to extra cover and takes a single.
yorker length delivery squeezed out down to mid-on.
nurdles it down behind square leg.
pushes to mid-off.
left alone outside the off stump.
stays back and defends to the off side.
flicked in the air down to long leg.
short ball and looking to pull, gets some part of body or glove and falls down on the ground, just misses the stumps.
goes for the pull and gets an under edge and McCullum could not get his gloves under it and the catch is spilled.
left alone through to the keeper.
nips back in and gets an inside edge through square leg.
full toss and driven nicely through mid-off to the fence.
way outside the off stump, left alone.
good length delivery defended to mid-on.
defended down the track.
defended once again down the track.
full toss and driven into the ground to mid-off.
lets it go outside the off stump.
slower delivery and the batsman pulls it down to long leg for a single.
slower delivery, glides it down to third man.
full on the leg and flicked in the air down to fine leg on the bounce.
once again he flicks it in the air down to fine leg and this time Franklin runs in and takes a good low catch.
deadly bouncer and Waller takes evasive action, just gets out of the line of the delivery.
another short delivery and Waller defends it down to the off side.
defended to the off side.
up on his toes and defends to point.
on the middle stump line. Taylor shuffles across and defends it back onto the pitch
on the leg stump. Taylor glances it to fine-leg for a single
short and wide outside the off stump. Waller being new to the crease is unable to judge the bounce and cuts it to the point fielder
outside the off stump. Waller looks to drive off the backfoot and is beaten
good length ball on the off stump. Waller comes forward and defends

short of a good length ball. Waller is again beaten by the bounce as he looks to cut it away. He does not get enough wood on it. Williamson dives to his left and spills, what is a tough chance at point
comes forward and pushes to mid-on for a single
wide down the leg side. McCullum has to dive to his left to prevent four more wides
good length ball outside the off stump. Taylor runs the bat over the ball and slices it to short third-man for a single
short ball on the off stump. Waller is in position to play the pull shot before the ball is bowled. He pulls it to deep midwicket
another wide down the leg side and they even run across
short ball outside the off stump. Waller keeps the bat close to the body and defends it with soft hands
good length ball outside the off stump. Waller has nothing to do with those deliveries
good length ball outside the off stump. Waller comes forward and defends it back onto the pitch
first sign of aggressive intent by Taylor. Franklin pitches it up, enough for Taylor to free his arms and loft the ball over long-on for a six
short ball on the off stump. Taylor turns it to fine-leg for a single
fuller ball outside the off stump. Waller slices it over point. Oram pulls off a diving stop to save two runs for his team. Hundred comes up for Zimbabwe
leg cutter on the middle stump. Waller presents a dead bat
on the leg stump. Taylor turns it to fine-leg for a single
runs it down to third man for a single
outside the off stump. Taylor looks to steer it to third-man. Can't find the gap though but Nicol misfields and gifts a single
comes forward and defends it to cover
now you can't get more luckier than this. Short ball on the off stump. Waller looks to pull it and gets a top edge that sails over the keeper's head for a boundary
off the pads to fine-leg for a leg-bye
fuller ball outside the off stump. Waller comes forward and cover drives it to sweeper boundary. Top Shot
this time Nicol pulls the length back as Waller has to defend it to the leg side
fuller on the off and middle. Waller see's the fine-leg fielder in and sweeps over him for another boundary in the over
comes forward and pushes it to mid-on for a single
is this the weak link in the Kiwi attack that Zimbabwe are searching for? Taylor comes down the track and lofts it to long-off for the third boundary of the over
make it 17 off the over as Nicol goes round the wicket and bowls a fuller ball on the middle stump. Taylor sweeps it to deep square leg for his second boundary in the over
comes forward and pushes it to midwicket for a single
fuller ball on the off stump. Taylor comes forward and pushes it back to the bowler
fuller ball on the off stump. Taylor comes forward and pushes it to  mid-on
fuller ball on the middle stump. Taylor comes forward and punches it down the ground for a couple. In the process he gets to his fifty and soaks in the warm applause of the crowd
pushes it to point and sets off for a quick single
the Bracewell from the slog overs of the previous game is back! He presents Waller with width outside the off stump. Waller cuts it in the air to the point boundary
defends it to the off side
fuller ball on the middle stump. Taylor comes forward and pushes it to long-on for a single
punches it to cover off the backfoot for a single
turns the face of the bat at the last moment as he gets a single to midwicket
wide down the leg side
pushes it to deep midwicket for a single
fuller ball on the off stump. Taylor leans forward and turns it to deep square-leg for a single
fuller ball outside the off stump. Taylor goes for the ugly swipe across to the leg side and gets an outside edge that falls short of the third-man fielder
wide outside the off stump
good length ball outside the off stump. Waller has nothing to do with it as he shoulders arms
low full-toss on the middle and leg. Waller flicks it stylishly to vacant deep square-leg region for a boundary
outside the off stump and left alone by Waller
cuts it to deep point for a single
short ball outside the off stump. Taylor rocks back in an attempt to pull and at the last moment decides to defend it
he begins with a wide down the leg side
fuller ball on the off stump. Waller turns it to midwicket for a single
fuller ball on the off stump again as Taylor pushes it down the ground for a single
fuller ball outside the off stump. Waller slices it to sweeper cover
fuller ball on the off stump. Taylor drives it to long-off for a single
good length ball on the off stump. Waller turns it to square-leg for a single
pushes it down the ground to long-on for a single
outside the off stump. Taylor lets it go as he thinks that the umpire will call it a wide. Oxenford doesn't and Taylor gives him the 'look'
outside the off stump and left alone
fuller ball on the leg stump. Taylor flicks but can't keep it down. In the end, he is lucky that it doesn't carry to the fine-leg fielder. He takes a single

short ball aimed at the ribs. Waller keeps the bat close to his body and upper cuts it. He doesn't time it well as it just falls short of the fielder, Franklin at third-man. The bounce beats Franklin as it results in a misfield. Waller gets a couple
effort ball outside the off stump. Waller lets it pass to the keeper
poor line and length as he overpitches it on the leg stump. Waller leans forward and glances it past short fine-leg for a boundary
pushes it to the midwicket for a single
defends it to the off side
short ball on the off stump. Waller stands tall and turns it to square-leg for a single
fuller ball on the off stump. Taylor stays back in the crease as he pushes it to mid-off and sets off for a quick single
fuller ball on the leg stump. Waller chips it wide of the long-on fielder for a couple
short ball outside the off stump. Waller looks to run it down to third-man. The late swing beats the outside edge
fuller ball outside the off stump. Taylor shuffles across and whips it to deep square-leg for a couple
short ball outside the off stump. Taylor runs it down to third-man for a single
wide outside the off stump

good length ball on the middle stump. Though he has the runs next to his name, Waller has struggled to pick the length today. This time too, he errs in picking the length and is early into the ugly hoick to midwicket. The ball hits the timber and Waller has to walk back
pushes it to mid-on to get off the mark
wide outside the off stump and not given by the umpire again
width outside the off stump and Taylor latches on. He moves back and across as he lofts it over the infield to the extra-cover boundary
comes forward and defends
pushes it to the off side for a single
short ball on the middle and leg. Taylor sees it early and guides it to the fine-leg boundary
pushes it to mid-on for a single
oversteps and bowls one on the leg stump. Chigumbura turns it to fine-leg for a single
fuller ball on the middle stump. Taylor clears the front foot and slogs it into the hands of Nicol at deep midwicket. HE can't dismissed as it is a free-hit. He gets a single for himself
comes forward and defends it to the off side
and begins the spell with a wide down the leg side
fuller ball outside the off stump. Taylor comes forward and defends it back onto the pitch
similar kind of a delivery as the previous one. Taylor though has aggressive intent as he walks across and whips it to deep midwicket for a boundary
fuller ball on the middle stump. Taylor forces it to mid-on for a single
good length ball on the off and middle. Chigumbura looks to defend it and gets an inside edge to square-leg for a single
slower ball on the off stump. Taylor comes forward and pushes it to mid-on with soft hands for a single
short ball outside the off stump. Chigumbura is shuffling across as the ball is being bowled. He picks the length at the last moment as he weaves out of the way
Taylor comes forward and drops the ball at his feet with soft hands. He sets off for a quick single
steers it to short third-man for a single
short outside the off stump. Taylor moves across and runs it to third-man for a single
short ball on the off and middle. Chigumbura drops the wrists down. The ball makes its way to the keeper. It looked like it was close to the gloves
short ball on the middle and leg. There is nothing that Chigumbura can do than to weave out of harms way
steers it to short third-man for a single
good length ball on the middle stump. Chigumbura comes forward and pushes it to midwicket
fuller ball on the leg stump. Chigumbura moves across and glances it fine for a boundary. Aldridge under pressure now
beats him with late swing
short ball outside the off stump. Chigumbura defends it back onto the pitch
good length ball outside the off stump. Chigumbura runs it down to third-man for a single
good length ball outside the off stump. Chigumbura looks to defend it on the off side and gets an inside edge back to the bowler
runs it down to third-man for a single
good length ball outside the off stump. Taylor's wrists must be sore with all the steering and turning today as he steers one more to short third-man for a single
comes down the track and drives it to cover
this time he comes down the track and drives it past cover for a single
fuller ball on the off stump. Taylor comes down the track and pushes it back to the bowler
defends it to the off side

short ball on the middle stump. Chigumbura looks to defend it and gets an inside edge. He is looking back to see if it hits the stumps and is slow in responding to Taylor's call. They get a single as McCullum can't pick the ball on the run
width outside the off stump. Invitation for Taylor to free his arms. He does that and lofts it over extra-cover for a boundary
pushes it to mid-off for a single
Chigumbura is beaten by a short-ball

McKay deceives Chigumbura with a fuller ball! Chigumbura is expecting a short delivery as he is waiting on the backfoot. McKay slips in a fuller ball outside the off stump. Chigumbura looks to drive though he is in no position to drive. He gets an inside edge onto the middle and leg stump
comes forward and pushes it to mid-on for a single
deceives him with a slower ball
good length ball outside the off stump. Meth defends it to the off side
short ball outside the off stump. Meth looks to pull it away and is beaten
good length ball outside the off stump. MEth comes forward and pushes it to cover for a single
good length ball on the middle stump. Taylor comes forward and defends it back onto the pitch
short ball outside the off stump. Meth looks to cut it away and is beaten by the away movement
good length ball on the middle stump. Meth pushes it to the leg side for a single
width outside the off stump again as Taylor slices it over cover for a single
opens the face of the bat as he drives it to sweeper cover for a single
full-toss outside the off stump. And a slower one too. The pace doesn't matter to Taylor as he comes down the track and pushes it to long-on for a couple
temporary lapse of concentration for Taylor as he chases a ball outside the off stump. It just about misses the outside edge
fuller ball on the off stump. Meth flicks it over fine-leg for a boundary
fuller ball outside the off stump. Taylor comes forward and pushes it to cover

fuller ball on the off stump. Taylor looks to put it away on the leg side. He gets a leading edge and Taylor is unaware of the ball's whereabouts. Meth calls him for a single. Williamson's throw is too quick for Bracewell as he has to take a few steps backwards to gather it. In the meanwhile Taylor makes it to the crease
flicks it to deep midwicket for a boundary
pushes it to long-on for a single
outside the off stump. Taylor looks to steer it but can't find the gap
this time he does as he steers it to deep point for a single
comes forward and defends it to the off side
fuller ball outside the off stump. Meth comes forward and drives it wide of the mid-off fielder. A late dive saves three runs for the team
short ball outside the off stump. Taylor plays it with soft hands to short third-man and runs across for a quick single
short ball outside the off stump. Taylor runs it down to third-man for a single
fuller ball on the off stump. Meth makes room and smashes it over mid-off for a boundary
comes forward and pushes it to mid-off for a quick single
short ball outside the off stump. Taylor steers it to third-man for a single

short ball on the middle and off. Meth pulls it right into the hands of deep midwicket fielder. Nothing much that he could have done really as Taylor with a hundred looming, isn't going for the strokes. It was all left to Meth and the pressure gets to him
fuller ball on the off stump. Taylor comes forward and defends it back to the bowler
good length ball outside the off stump. Utseya looks to run it down to third-man and the late swing beats him
fuller ball outside the off stump. Utseya goes across the line and swings it over wide long-on for a huge six
short outside the off stump. Utseya plays it to point
Utseya is on the off stump as he pushes it to cover for a single
short ball outside the off stump. Taylor looks to cut it but doesn't get the meatier part of his bat on it as the ball trickles to the point fielder
Taylor lets a simple short ball go waste. He looks to cut and is beaten
good length ball outside the off stump. Utseya moves across to play it on the leg side and gets an outside edge back to the keeper
pushes it to cover and sets off for a quick single
Taylor becomes the first Zimbabwean to get back to back hundreds. He paddles a fuller ball on the off stump to fine-leg for a boundary
fuller ball outside the off stump. Taylor feasts on the width as he lofts it over mid-off for a superb boundary
short ball on the off stump. Taylor does play the pull shot with some force but can't beat the fielder at deep midwicket
Price does as he crunches it past deep midwicket for a boundary. That's a good over to finish the innings

dropped by Chigumbura, driven in the air to the left of the bowler and he drops it.

cuts hard to the sweeper on the off side.

a beauty, pitches and comes in and McCullum plays all around it.

gets behind the delivery and defends to mid-on.
short ball and pulled in the air over the square leg umpire to the deep.
pushes down the ground to long on.
once again Waller drops a catch, flicked in the air to deep square leg and Waller makes a mess of the catch.
hit high once again, but this time over the square leg fence for a six.

short ball pulled to the midwicket fence.
